getUnderlyingDriver

private java.sql.Driver getUnderlyingDriver(java.lang.String url)
                                     throws java.sql.SQLException
Given a WRAPPER_URL_PREFIX type URL, find the underlying driver that accepts the URL.

Parameters:
url - JDBC connection URL.
Returns:
Underlying driver for the given URL. Null is returned if the URL is not a WRAPPER_URL_PREFIX type URL or there is no underlying driver that accepts the URL.
Throws:
java.sql.SQLException - if a database access error occurs.

acceptsURL

public boolean acceptsURL(java.lang.String url)
                   throws java.sql.SQLException
Typically, drivers will return true if they understand the subprotocol specified in the URL and false if they don't. This driver's protocols start with WRAPPER_URL_PREFIX
